          <div class="article__desc">In 1933, Arsenal first took to the field in red shirts with white sleeves, the latter feature added by their famously innovative manager Herbert Chapman so that his players could spot their team-mates more easily. The Arsenal 23/24 Home Jersey pays tribute to the 2003/04 Invincibles, who won the Premier League and remained unbeaten all season, with gold trim and a lightning-bolt detail. Because lightning surely couldn’t strike twice…</div>
