          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Nick Brown’s unique Arsenal book recognises the club’s premier marksmen. Subtitled Every Goal from Arsenal’s Greatest Ever Scorers, it catalogues the goals of the 19 players to score 100 times or more for the club. Heading the list are two men synonymous with red and white: Thierry Henry – the leading goalscorer in the club’s history with 228 – and Ian Wright. They are joined by stars of every decade from Theo Walcott and Olivier Giroud to Cliff Bastin and David Jack, while another centurion, Alan Smith, has written the foreword.</div>
