   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--">
      
      Arsenal books – autobiographies
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock  fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">Arsene Wenger, Dennis Bergkamp and Tony Adams are among the Highbury heroes whose autobiographies feature in this selection of Arsenal books written by those players and managers who have left an indelible mark on the club.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97814711/9781471156755.jpg" alt="Sober : Football. My Story. My Life."></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Tony-Adams/Sober--Football-My-Story-My-Life/18097077">Sober : Football. My Story. My Life.</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Tony Adams’ autobiography follows on from Addicted, his searingly honest account of his battle with alcoholism. Having given up drinking in August 1996, he experienced another significant change two months later when Arsene Wenger was made Arsenal manager, bringing with him revolutionary ideas about diet, preparation and training. The former Arsenal captain tells how the Frenchman influenced his thinking about the game and his move into coaching and management, and discusses his continuing recovery and why he set up Sporting Chance, the charity that supports sportspeople suffering from addictions.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Tony-Adams/Sober--Football-My-Story-My-Life/18097077">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97814711/9781471129537.jpg" alt="Stillness and Speed : My Story"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Dennis-Bergkamp/Stillness-and-Speed--My-Story/15809118">Stillness and Speed : My Story</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Dennis Bergkamp’s autobiography unmasks some of the mystery of the most creative footballer in Arsenal’s history. Previously, the Dutchman preferred to let his football do the talking, but this reflection on his career is as eloquent as any and footage of him in action. As a youngster at Ajax, Bergkamp learnt his trade from the greatest Dutch player of them all, Johan Cruyff, but it was at Highbury, especially after the arrival of a fellow visionary in manager Arsene Wenger, that he became a truly inspirational and influential player.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Dennis-Bergkamp/Stillness-and-Speed--My-Story/15809118">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="https://www.telegraph.co.uk/content/dam/eip/particles/gen/2023/11/09/252450e7-7136-484d-939a-8d9987a37098.png" alt="Arsenal retro 88-89 away shirt"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=296X1634315&xs=1&url=https%3A%2F%2Farsenaldirect.arsenal.com%2FMens%2FArsenal-Retro-Collection%2FArsenal-Retro-88-89-Away-Shirt%2Fp%2FA9878">Arsenal retro 88-89 away shirt</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Friday May 26, 1989 is a date etched in the minds of all Arsenal fans of a certain vintage. The 2-0 win away to Liverpool that night – sealed by Michael Thomas’s goal with almost the last kick of the match, ended an 18-year wait for the First Division title in the most dramatic fashion. The iconic yellow shirt worn at Anfield by club legends such as Tony Adams, Paul Merson and David Rocastle makes the ideal Arsenal gift for fans of all ages.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=296X1634315&xs=1&url=https%3A%2F%2Farsenaldirect.arsenal.com%2FMens%2FArsenal-Retro-Collection%2FArsenal-Retro-88-89-Away-Shirt%2Fp%2FA9878">Add to Basket</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97814746/9781474618267.jpg" alt="My Life in Red and White"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Arsene-Wenger/My-Life-in-Red-and-White--The-Sunday-Times-Number-One-Bes/25453423">My Life in Red and White</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">It feels like underselling this book simply to call it an Arsene Wenger autobiography. The Frenchman achieved so much more than building successful and attractive teams for 22 years as manager of Arsenal, playing a central role in the club’s move from Highbury to the Emirates Stadium and maintaining its financial health. His reflections on his approach to the game will appeal to fans of all clubs, while management and business leaders will take something from his strategies for success. Wenger also discusses the unrest that led to his resignation from Arsenal and his role as Fifa’s chief of global football development.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Arsene-Wenger/My-Life-in-Red-and-White--The-Sunday-Times-Number-One-Bes/25453423">Add to Basket</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97800086/9780008646479.jpg" alt="Revolution: The Rise of Arteta’s Arsenal"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Charles-Watts/Revolution--The-Rise-of-Artetas-Arsenal/28402234">Revolution: The Rise of Arteta’s Arsenal</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Charles Watts’ portrait of Mikel Arteta charts the transformative effect the man from the Basque Country has had on Arsenal. It examines the managerial philosophy that has given the club back not just its status as title contenders but also as a team who play fast-paced, attractive football. Although he led them to a record 14th FA Cup victory after just eight months in charge, Arteta’s revolution has encompassed a pandemic, supporter discontent and its share of disappointments. Earmarked while at Barcelona as ‘a player in the mould of Pep Guardiola’, Arteta is turning out to be the biggest rival to his old boss.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Charles-Watts/Revolution--The-Rise-of-Artetas-Arsenal/28402234">Add to Basket</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--center">
      
      Arsenal books – other titles
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock padding fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">Looking for a unique Arsenal book? These titles include the club&rsquo;s official annual, quiz books to test your knowledge of all things red and white, and Nick Hornby&rsquo;s memorable account of how he lost his heart to the Gunners.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97801413/9780141391816.jpg" alt="Fever Pitch"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Nick-Hornby/Fever-Pitch/11377709">Fever Pitch</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">More Arsenal love story than Arsenal book, Nick Hornby’s memoir launched his career as a writer in 1992. In this case, his devotion to the Gunners stems not from a chance meeting but a boyhood trip to Highbury with his father. Over the years – and numerous Saturday afternoon and midweek dates – his relationship with Arsenal embraces familiar highs and lows. Attraction, adoration, loyalty, pain, hope, disappointment and the rare moments of joy that come when your team win silverware are all etched in this diary of a fan. The final result? A brilliant, skilfully crafted study of football’s hold on those who fall under its spell.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Nick-Hornby/Fever-Pitch/11377709">Add to Basket</a></div>          
      </div>
